This directory contains the original upstream gzstream import together with the
PandA/Bambu-maintained header-only derivative used by the repository build.

Directory structure
-------------------
- `gzstream.h`, `gzstream.C`, `README`, `COPYING.LIB`, `index.html`, tests, and
  related assets are the preserved upstream distribution.
- `gzstream.hpp` is the PandA/Bambu-maintained derivative of that code. It keeps
  the project-specific improvements and compiler-compatibility updates that have
  accumulated over time.

Why this refactoring
--------------------
Keeping the maintained derivative in this directory:

- keeps it next to the upstream sources it derives from;
- makes the provenance of local changes clearer;
- keeps the third-party-derived component grouped with the rest of the import;
- lets the build resolve `gzstream.hpp` from `ext/gzstream/` directly.
